This isn't the only problem. Not all gifs and jpegs use that MIME [1]. Try this:<p><pre><code>   $allowed_image_types = array('image/gif', 'image/x-gif', 'image/pjpeg', 'image/jpeg',  'image/x-pjpeg', 'image/x-jpeg', 'image/x-jpg',  'image/jpg');
   if (!in_array($type, $allowed_image_types)) {
   	$error = 'ERROR: You can only upload GIF and JPG files.';
   }
</code></pre>
